Package: biparty
Title: Congressional Bipartisanship Scores by Member and Issue Area
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(given = "Anonymous",
           family = "Author",
           email = "anonymous@noreply.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")))
Description: Provides Congressional Bipartisanship Scores (CBS) for all
    members of the U.S. House and Senate from 1983 to 2024, spanning the
    98th through 118th Congresses. Scores are constructed from more than
    2.4 million cosponsorship decisions on 147,669 bills and capture two
    distinct forms of bipartisan behavior: attracting original out-party
    cosponsors to a member's own bills and offering original cosponsorships
    to out-party-sponsored bills. The package includes aggregate scores and
    issue-specific scores across 34 Congressional Research Service (CRS)
    policy areas, in both raw and precision-weighted (empirical-Bayes
    shrinkage) variants, for 2,056 unique legislators and 11,549
    legislator-term observations. Member-level identifier crosswalks
    (Bioguide, GovTrack, THOMAS, ICPSR, Wikipedia, Wikidata) are included
    directly in the score datasets to facilitate merging with other
    congressional data sources. Scores are introduced and described in
    Authors (2026). This project was supported by an anonymous funding
    source.
